a87600dc-8bb3-4c5f-93e1-ab7394b39026.0102872c-6d73-4570-bff9-591b6144d9da.description=Description\:

This step prepares the server wrapper for other steps to use.

Dependencies\: None

Return Code\:

0 \= Step ran successfully.
1 \= Step failed.

Inputs\:
 command - executes PrepareOracleServer.py
 Server.Become User - No description
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 No Value - Empty mapping for future steps.
 Server Wrapper - String to execute routine as server superuser.

 a87600dc-8bb3-4c5f-93e1-ab7394b39026.01909d7c-bf2d-4b5f-b221-2fda3be56a9b.description=Description\:

This step verifies the installation of Oracle Database software.

Dependencies\: Must run as the instance user.

Return Code\: 

0 \= Verified Oracle installation.
1 \= Error encountered during step execution.

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyProvisionOracleSoftwarev2.py
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: String to execute routine as instance superuser.
 Inventory Location - Required\: Directory location of Oracle inventory path.
 Oracle Home - Required\: The ORACLE_HOME install to verify.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Oracle Executable Size - Size in bytes of the Oracle executable.
 SQLPlus Version - Version of SQLPlus from Oracle Home.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 a87600dc-8bb3-4c5f-93e1-ab7394b39026.0d52adc1-3895-4bde-88f3-18ae24756941.description=Description\: 

This step verifies the Oracle Software by locating the installer (runInstaller), the product inventory (products.xml), the default response files, and the rootpre.sh script.

Dependencies\: The step will need to be run as the instance call wrapper.

Return Code\:

0 \= All required items were found in the install directory
1 \= At least one error occurred in this step.

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyOracleInstallSoftware.py
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: The Jython call wrapper required to run as the oracle user.
 Oracle Install Directory - Required\: Fully-qualified pathname of the Oracle Install Software.
 RAC One Node Option - Optional\: Set to True to install Oracle RAC One Node software using the oracle.install.db.isRACOneInstall option. The default is False.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Default Response Files - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified pathnames of the response files (*.rsp) files found in the install directory.
 Oracle Installer - The fully-qualified pathname of the Oracle installer executable.
 Oracle Products File - The fully-qualified pathname of the products.xml file.
 RootPre Location - The fully-qualified pathname of the rootpre.sh file.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

This step prepares the call wrappers needed to become the owner of the Oracle Database software and root. It sets the default values for call wrapper and Oracle OS owner variables used in subsequent workflow steps.

Return code\:

1 \= At least one parameter is not valid

Inputs\:
 command - executes PrepareOracleCallWrapper.py

 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Boolean False - Boolean value for False
 Boolean True - Boolean value for True
 Instance Wrapper - Jython call wrapper to run as the Oracle Instance owner.
 No Value - Used to hide unused parameters in later steps.
 None Value - Value containing None

 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

This step installs the Oracle software as defined by the response file.

1 \= At least one error occurred in this step.

 command - executes ExecuteOracleSoftwareInstallerv2.py

 Instance Wrapper - Required\: The jython call wrapper required to run as the oracle user.
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the ORACLE_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed. For example, 'sqlnet.ora,ldap.ora,...' etc.
 Oracle Account - Deprecated, unused.
 Oracle Home - Required\: Fully-qualified pathname where the Oracle Home will be.
 Oracle Home Name - Required\: The name of the Oracle Home.
 Oracle Inventory - Required\: The fully-qualified name for the Oracle inventory file.

 Temporary File Location - Required\: The location where all temporary output files will be placed.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

This step validates all parameters needed for the Provision Oracle Software workflow.

Dependencies\: Run as instance owner.

Return Code\:

0 \= All files were found on the system.
1 \= Errors occurred while checking files.

Inputs\:
 command - executes GatherParametersforProvisionOracleSoftware.py
 Oracle Account - Optional (required only if inventory does not exist)\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home.
 Oracle Base - Required\: The fully-qualified path to the Oracle base directory where the admin directories will be located.
 Oracle Home - Required\: Fully-qualified pathname where the Oracle Home will be created. If the specified directory does not exist, it will be created.
 Oracle Software - Required\: Comma-separated list of relative or fully-qualified path names of the Oracle Database software archive files. If a fully-qualified path name points to a file, that file is expected to be on the target. If a relative path name points to a file, that file will be downloaded from the software repository. If a fully-qualified path name is a directory, the software is expected to be unzipped and ready to be applied.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 No Value - No value to map for the advanced parameters.
 Oracle Account - Oracle user that will own the ORACLE_HOME.athname of the OUI response file.
 Oracle Base - The fully-qualified path to the Oracle base directory where the admin directories will be located.
 Oracle Home - Fully-qualified pathname where the Oracle Home will be created. If the specified directory does not exist, it will be created.
 Oracle Software - Comma-separated list of relative or fully-qualified path names of the Oracle Database software archive files. If a fully-qualified path name points to a file, that file is expected to be on the target. If a relative path name points to a file, that file will be downloaded from the software repository. If a fully-qualified path name is a directory, the software is expected to be unzipped and ready to be applied.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 a87600dc-8bb3-4c5f-93e1-ab7394b39026.3f9780a1-3a9d-4d28-a5f6-a5daf88f5b5b.description=Description\:

This step validates all parameters needed for the Provision Oracle Software workflow.

Dependencies\: Run as instance owner.

Return Code\:

0 \= All files were found on the system.
1 \= Errors occurred while checking files.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ValidateProvisionOracleSoftwarev2.py
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 Cluster Nodes - Optional\: Comma-separated list of nodes to install software on. Leave blank for non-clustered environments.
 DBA Group - Optional\: The DBA group to use for superuser access to the subsequent Oracle Database (typically dba). If not specified, derived from the Oracle OS user.
 Download Location - Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software repository (only used if required files are not found on target but are found in the software directory).
 Enable DNFS - Optional\: When set to 'True' then the workflow will enable the Direct NFS option as part of the Software Installation.
 Extract Location - Optional\: Directory location where the Oracle Database software archives will be extracted. Will be cleaned up at end of workflow execution. If not specified, a default will be created.
 Install Edition - Optional\: The install edition of the Oracle installation. Valid values are SE or EE. The default is EE.
 Install Response - Optional\: Location of the Oracle Universal Installer (OUI) response file.
 Inventory Groups - Required\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory groups. One for each Inventory Pointer.
 Inventory Pointers - Required\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pointer files.
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the ORACLE_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed. For example, 'sqlnet.ora,ldap.ora,...' etc.
 Operator Group - Optional\: The operator group to use for operator access to the subsequent Oracle Database (typically oper). If this parameter is not specified, it is derived from the Oracle OS user.
 Oracle Account - Required\: Oracle user that will own the ORACLE_HOME.
 Oracle Base - Optional\: The fully-qualified path to the Oracle base directory where the admin directories will be located.
 Oracle Home - Required\: Fully-qualified pathname where the Oracle Home will be created. If the specified directory does not exist, it will be created.
 Oracle Home Info - Dictionary list of all information discovered in the supplied inventory file(s).
 Oracle Home Name - Optional\: The Oracle Home name. If not specified, it is randomly generated.
 Oracle Software - Required\: Comma-separated list of relative or fully-qualified path names of the Oracle Database software archive files. If a fully-qualified path name points to a file, that file is expected to be on the target. If a relative path name points to a file, that file will be downloaded from the software repository. If a fully-qualified path name is a directory, the software is expected to be unzipped and ready to be applied.
 RAC One Node Install - Optional\: Set to true to install Oracle RAC One Node software using the oracle.install.db.isRACOneInstall option. The default is false.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.

 password - Login information for host

 protocol - ssh/wmi

 Cluster Nodes - Comma-separated list of nodes to install software on.

 Download From - No description
 Downloaded Files - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified pathnames of files downloaded from the software repository.
 Enable DNFS - When set to 'True' then the workflow will enable the Direct NFS option as part of the Software Installation.
 Extract Location - Directory location where the Oracle Database software archives will be extracted.
 FileNames - Comma-separated list of files that download step will use to copy from the software repository.
 Install Edition - The install edition of the Oracle installation. Valid values are SE or EE. The default is EE.

 a87600dc-8bb3-4c5f-93e1-ab7394b39026.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow installs Oracle Database software on a server in the location specified by the _Oracle Home_ parameter. The workflow can be customized to provision an Oracle Standalone, Grid Standalone, or CRS RAC environment.

 Description

This workflow installs Oracle Database software on a server using the runinstaller utility supplied by Oracle.

To use this workflow, you must provide the Oracle Database software in one of the following forms\:

 - A software archive (ZIP or cpio.gz file) that exists on the software repository or on the target machine
 - Unarchived files on a CD, DVD, NFS mount, or similar device

If the inventory pointer is not found, it is created.

If you do not provide a response file, a default response file is created from the response files included in the software archive. This default response file will install Oracle Database Standard Edition.



 Dependencies

Oracle Operating Systems prerequisites are met. See "http\://docs.oracle.com"\:http\://docs.oracle.com

 How to Specify the Oracle Software Archive(s)

You can specify the Oracle Database software archive(s) three different ways\: 

 Method 1\: The Oracle ZIP file (or files) is in the software repository (Provisioning/Software)\:


NOTE\: The Oracle ZIP files must be downloaded from Oracle. Example\: p10404530_112030_Linux-x86-64_1of7.zip, p10404530_112030_Linux-x86-64_2of7.zip


\# In the _Oracle Software_ parameter, specify the name (or names) of the ZIP file (or files) downloaded from Oracle.
\# In the _Download Location_ parameter, specify the directory where the ZIP file (or files) specified in the _Oracle Software_ parameter should be downloaded. 
\# In the _Software Archive_ parameter, specify the directory where the ZIP file (or files) specified in the _Oracle Software_ parameter should be extracted (unzipped).


All downloaded files are removed upon successful completion of the workflow.


 Method 2\: The Oracle ZIP file (or files) is stored on each target machine\:


NOTE\: The ZIP file must be downloaded from Oracle. Example\: 10201_database_linux32.zip


\# In the _Oracle Software_ parameter, specify the fully qualified name (or names) of the ZIP file (or files) downloaded from Oracle. 
\# Do not specify a value for the _Download Location_ parameter. You must specify the _Download Location_ if the _Install Response_ needs to be downloaded; otherwise, do not specify a value for _Download Location_.


All downloaded files are removed upon successful completion of the workflow.


 Method 3\: The unzipped Oracle archive is stored on each target machine\:


\# In the _Oracle Software_ parameter, specify the fully qualified directory name where the unzipped files are located. 
\# Do not specify a value for the _Software Archive_ or _Download Location_ parameters. You must specify the _Download Location_ if the _Install Response_ needs to be downloaded; otherwise, do not specify a value for _Download Location_.


 Usage Instructions

Review the input parameters listed below, and create a deployment using values appropriate for your environment. Workflow should be run on a host after provisioning CRS and ASM if using RAC, after Oracle Grid Infrastructure for Standalone Server, or the first workflow if planning on using Oracle Standalone Database.


 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Oracle Base - Required\: The fully-qualified path to the Oracle base directory where the admin directories will be located.
 Oracle Home - Required\: Fully-qualified pathname where the Oracle Home will be created. If the specified directory does not exist, it will be created.
 Oracle Software - Required\: Comma-separated list of relative or fully-qualified path names of the Oracle Database software archive files. If a fully-qualified path name points to a file, that file is expected to be on the target. If a relative path name points to a file, that file will be downloaded from the software repository. If a fully-qualified path name is a directory, the software is expected to be unzipped and ready to be applied.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Become User - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Download Location - Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software repository. This is only used if the required files are not found on target server but are found in the software repository.
 Install Response - Optional\: Location of the Oracle Universal Installer (OUI) response file.
 Operator Group - Optional\: The operator group to use for operator access to the subsequent Oracle Database (typically oper). If this parameter is not specified, it is derived from the Oracle OS user.
 Install Edition - Optional\: The install edition of the Oracle installation. Valid values are SE or EE. The default is EE.
 Oracle Home Name - Optional\: The Oracle Home name. If not specified, it is randomly generated.
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the ORACLE_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 RAC One Node Install - Optional\: Set to true to install Oracle RAC One Node software using the oracle.install.db.isRACOneInstall option. The default is false.
 DBA Group - Optional\: The DBA group to use for superuser access to the subsequent Oracle Database (typically dba). If not specified, derived from the Oracle OS user.
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 Oracle Account - Optional (required only if inventory does not exist)\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home.
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 Cluster Nodes - Optional\: Comma-separated list of nodes to install software on. Leave blank for non-clustered environments.
 Extract Location - Optional\: Directory location where the Oracle database software archives will be extracted. Will be cleaned up at end of workflow execution. If not specified, a default will be created.
 Enable DNFS - Optional\: When set to 'True' then the workflow will enable the Direct NFS option as part of the Software Installation.

 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The Output tab will indicate whether the software installation was successful. 

To further verify the results\:

\# Log in to the target server.
\# Set your ORACLE_HOME variable to the installed Oracle Home.
\# Run the command\: ls $ORACLE_HOME/bin
\# Verify that all the standard binaries are installed, such as sqlplus, lsnrctl, and srvctl.
